    <title>Refugees contributor: Peter Tinti and Tuesday Reitano</title>
    <description>Peter Tinti is an independent journalist and senior research fellow at the Global Initiative Against Transnational Organized Crime. 
Formerly based in west Africa, Tuesday Reitano has been studying organized crime networks and their impact on governance, conflict and development for more than 20 years, both in the United Nations system and at the Global Initiative, which she co-founded. She is based in Beirut, Lebanon.
</description>
